    <p>
      It started with a simple voice note:  
      <em>"I want a pair of rings I can wear every day, nothing too much, but with a story. Something about the sea, the sky, and a little starlight.”</em>
    </p>
    <p>
      Those few words instantly set my mind adrift. I began doodling gentle wave curves on paper, letting the lines run free like a tide—sometimes swirling, sometimes just quietly flowing. We talked about how life can feel both vast and light, like clouds drifting above the ocean. So, I added tiny diamonds, each catching the light like a star you’d spot on a night walk by the sea.
    </p>
