      But it wasn’t finished. The client messaged me: <em>“Can we add a fishtail somewhere? Just a hint, not obvious.”</em><br>
      I loved that idea. A tiny fishtail, barely noticeable, now tucked into the band—just for her. The ring became something between freedom and daily comfort, a piece that never shouts but always moves.
    </p>
    <figure>
